CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 7, 1961, pg. A31 reads: "Winners All - Winners and runners-up in the annual Dandy Duffer Club tournament are shown with their trophies, which were presented at the club's Awards Night, recently, at the Vogue Terrace. Left to right, back row: Louis Johnson, James Wise, John Trent, James Chapman Jr., Dave Goodman, Warren Breyard, Andrew Dent, Joseph Preston and Harvey Gravely.  Seated: Jack Ethridge, Wilbur (Mickey) Lewis, Jack Grover, club champion; Charles Hinton and James Dyer.  Kneeling, forefront, is tournament director William Browne, who made the presentations. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Dandy Duffer Club winners, from left, kneeling: William Browne; seated: Jack Ethridge, Wilbur (Mickey) Lewis, Jack Grover, Charles Hinton, and James Dyer; back row: Louis Johnson, James Wise, John Trent, James Chapman Jr., Dave Goodman, Warren Breyard, Andrew Dent, Joseph Preston, and Harvey Gravely, posed with trophies in Vogue Terrace, East McKeesport, another version
